I just paid for the full version and when you try to trace the letter 10 it only let's you trace the one and freezes when you try to face the zero. Very dissappointed. Wasted my money

I love that my son can spend time learning how to write his numbers properly. I spent the money to purchase the app so that he would have access to educational apps on my phone and his tablet. I want him to spend time learning instead of just playing games. This app accomplishes both of my missions: to keep him busy and learning. It is great for keeping him occupied at the doctors office too.

I'm still trying to figure out how to create a profile for my kid. The app picuters are misleading, I thought I was getting letters too. I paid $2.99 to get 1-10 which is garbage. And because this is a stupid android tablet I can't see the full screen because of the dumb bar thing at the bottom. I hate it.

I don't like paying for an app only to be bombarded by advertising for other apps by the same developer,  especially when it's my 3yr old daughter who is being bombarded.  Remove the advertising and I'd give it 5 stars.

This app teaches basics math as easy as 1,2, 3 in a fun and interactive way. Number Tracing improves the child's fine motor skills, while they master the sounds and phonics through the crisp and appealing voice of command. A great app for toddlers and preschoolers while they play, they also learn.
screen is cut on down side. need to fix it. But, this app is very good for my child.
